wn)\n* [[Orange (fruit)|Orange]]\n* [[Strawberry]] (pink)\n* [[Vanilla]] (beige)\n* [[Vanilla]] Swirl (orange)\n| Mainly sold in [[Convenience store|bodegas/convenience stores]] in urban cities\n| 2010<ref name=\"typetive.com\">[http://www.typetive.com/candyblog/category/skittles Blog items categorized as \"Skittles\"] at Candy Blog on typetive.com</ref> \n|-\n|Carnival \n|\n* [[Bubble Gum]] (pink)\n* [[Candy Apple]] (light yellow)\n* [[Cotton Candy]] (baby blue)\n* [[Liquorice]] (red)\n* [[Slush (beverage)|Green Slushy]] (green)\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}} ended in 2010/2011\n|-\n|Skittles Unlimited\n|\n* [[Bubblegum]] (baby blue)\n* [[Doughnut|Jam Doughnut]] (brown red)\n* [[Popcorn]] (light yellow)\n* [[Toffee]] [[Apple]] (green)\n|In 2011, Limited Edition Carnival Skittles were re-released as 'Skittles Unlimited' \nSold in [[Canada]] in blued packaging as a limited edition.\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n| Double Sour \n|\n* [[Apple|Sour Green Apple]] (green)\n* [[Lemon|Sour Lemon]] (yellow)\n* [[Raspberry|Sour Blue Raspberry]] (blue)\n* [[Strawberry|Sour Strawberry]] (red)\n* [[Watermelon|Sour Watermelon]] (pink)\n|These types of Skittles are coated with a double portion of very sour [[citric acid]] crystals.\nLike Sour Skittles, this product is sold in either bright green bags or boxes.\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|Extreme Fruit<br />Gum\n|\n* [[Blue raspberry flavor|Blue Raspberry]] (blue)\n* [[Cherry|Wild Cherry]] (red)\n* [[Apple|Green Apple]] (green)\n* [[Tangerine]] (orange)\n* [[Watermelon]] (pink)\n|These Skittles have the same flavors as Extreme Fruit Skittles Bubble Gum. \nComes in either black bags or boxes.\n| 2006<ref name=\"Wrigley\" />\n|-\n|Mint \n|\n* [[Spearmint]]\n* [[Wintergreen]]\n| Unlike ordinary Skittles, they came in plastic containers instead of bags.<ref name=\"cpu\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allbusiness.com/manufacturing/food-manufacturing-sugar/202056-1.html |title=Mint Skittles. (Candy Product Update). |date=2012-06-01 |accessdate=2009-07-11 |publisher=Confectioner |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100112140725/http://www.allbusiness.com/manufacturing/food-manufacturing-sugar/202056-1.html |archivedate=January 12, 2010 }}</ref>\n|2013\n|-\n|Skittles Mints\n|\n* Cool Mint (blue)\n* [[Peppermint]] (white)\n* [[Toffee]] Mint (green-brown)\n* [[Spearmint]] (dark green)\n* Sweet Mint (pale green)\n|A variety of mint-flavored Skittles, different from Mint Skittles, sold for a time in [[Europe]].\nInstead of the usual bag or plastic containers,<br />\nthey were sold in a 55-gram (1.94-oz) deep turquoise-colored box.\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|[[Extra (gum)|Extra]] Chewy Mints\n|\n* Cool Mint (white)\n* [[Peppermint]] (blue)\n* [[Spearmint]] (green)\n* Sweet Mint (sea green)\n|Revival of the Skittles Mints under the \"Extra\" brand, with all flavors but \"Toffee Mint\" included. Later renamed as just \"Chewy Mints\"\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|Chocolate \n|\n* [[Hot chocolate|Hot Chocolate]] (white, later red)\n* [[Types of chocolate|Milk Chocolate]] (brown)\n* [[Cafe mocha|Mocha Chocolate]] (green)\n* [[Chocolate|Nutty Chocolate]] (tan)\n* [[Chocolate|Wild Chocolate]] (blue)\n| Sold in 1.94 oz (55&nbsp;g) bags just like [[M&M's]].\n| 2008<ref name=\"Wrigley\" />\n|-\n|Chocolate Mix \n|\n* [[Chocolate]] [[Caramel]] ([[brown]])\n* [[Chocolate brownie|Brownie Batter]] (dark brown/[[black]])\n* [[Pudding|Chocolate Pudding]] ([[Auburn (color)|auburn]])\n* [[S'more]]s ([[Copper (color)|copper]])\n* [[Vanilla]] (off-white/[[Buff (color)|buff]])\n| Packaged in brown bags and boxes.\n| 2007<ref name=\"typetive.com\"/>\n|-\n|Liquorice \n|\n* Black [[Liquorice]] (black)\n* Liquorice [[Aniseed]] (green)\n* Liquorice Mint (white)\n* Liquorice Spice (red)\n* Liquorice [[Vanilla]] (orange)\n|These were sold in [[Europe]] in 55-gram (1.94-oz) boxes instead of the usual bags.\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|Citrus\n|\n* [[Mandarin Orange]] (light orange)\n* [[Pink Grapefruit]] (pink)\n* [[Lemon]] (yellow)\n* [[Lime (fruit)|Lime]] (green)\n* [[Orange (fruit)|Orange]] (dark orange)\n|Sold in [[Australia]] with Orange wrapping.\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|Fresh Mint \n|\n* [[Mint (candy)|Mint]]\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|Skittles Sensations\n|\n* Chili Berry (red)\n* [[Raspberry|Cool Raspberry]] (blue)\n* [[Orange (fruit)|Juicy Orange]] (orange)\n* [[Lemon|Lemon Tingle]] (yellow)\n* [[Apple|Sour Apple]] (green)\n|Skittles with 'hot' and 'cool' flavors.\n| 2009\n|-\n|Skittles Fizzl'd Fruits \n|\n* [[Berry]] [[Punch (drink)|Punch]] (violet)\n* [[Melon]] [[Berry]] (green)\n* [[Raspberry]] (blue)\n* [[Strawberry]] (pink)\n* [[Cherry|Wild Cherry]] (red)\n|Wild Berry Skittles with fizzing powder coating. Discontinued in 2012 due to low sales.\n|2010<ref name=\"typetive.com\"/>\n|-\n|Skittles Blenders\n|\n* [[Strawberry]] [[Lime (fruit)|Lime]] Blast (pink)\n* [[Cherry]] Tropicolada (red)\n* [[Green]] [[Apple]] [[Watermelon]] Freeze (green)\n* [[Mango]] [[Lemonade]] Blast (peach)\n* [[Melon]] [[Berry]] Blast (blue)\n|Skittles with two flavors blended together.\n|2011.<ref name=\"typetive.com\"/> Discontinued in 2014\n|-\n| Skittles Riddles\n|\n* [[Watermelon]] \n* [[Cherry]] \n* [[Punch (drink)|Punch]] \n* [[Apple]] \n* [[Raspberry]] \n|Skittles with colors that don't match the flavors. They were similar to the 2008 Confused Skittles from the UK, where the same colored shell can contain different flavors. A green piece may be apple in one bag, and cherry in another. Colors include red, pink, green, teal, and blue.\n|2012. Marketed as 'Confused Skittles' in the [[United Kingdom]]. Discontinued in 2014 (US)\n|-\n| Skittles Darkside\n|\n* Wicked [[Pomegranate]]/Black [[Cherry]] (2019) (Red)\n* Forbidden Fruit (US)(Blue)/Sweet Strawberry (UK) (Purple)\n* Midnight Lime (Green)\n* Dark Berry (US)(Purple)/ Dark Berry (UK) (Blue)\n* [[Blood orange|Blood Orange]] (Orange)\n|Skittles with a slight bold fruit taste. Was launched in the [[United Kingdom]] in 2015 as a limited edition flavor.\n|2013. Discontinued in 2015, returned seasonally in [[United