low)\n|Skittles with Halloween Themed/spooky flavors\n|Halloween 2016, 2017, 2018, and 2019\n|-\n| Skittles Brightside\n|\n*Paradise Punch (Blue)\n*Kiwi Banana (Yellow)\n*Tangerine (Orange)\n*Watermelon (Green)\n*Pink Lemonade (Pink)\n|Skittles with vivid bright colors. Found in some [[Walmarts]] in October 2016, expected for a nationwide release 2017\n|2017\n|-\n| Skittles Fruits & Sours\n|\n*Strawberry (Red)\n*Lime (Green)\n*Blackcurrant (Purple)\n*Sour Mandarin (Orange)\n*Sour Pineapple (Yellow)\n*Sour Raspberry (Pink)\n|Mixture of 3 flavors from Fruits and Crazy Sours flavors. Limited Edition in the [[United Kingdom]].\n|Early-Mid 2017\n|-\n| Skittles Pride Fruits\n|\n*Strawberry\n*Orange\n*Blackcurrant\n*Lemon\n*Lime\n|Fruit Skittles all in white to celebrate Pride Month once a year in the [[United Kingdom]].\n|June 2017-\n|-\n| Skittles Trick Plays\n| \n*Comeback Cherry\n*Audible Apple\n*Raspberry Rush\n*Strawberry Sneak\n*For-the-Win Watermelon\n|Limited edition US release in partnership with the [[National Football League]]. <br /> Colors don't match the flavors (colors are pink, light green, teal, blue, and red).\n|Fall 2017\n|-\n| Skittles Sweet Heat (US)\n|\n*Fiery Watermelon (Pink)\n*Blazin' Mango (Light Orange)\n*Flamin' Orange (Orange)\n*Sizzlin' Strawberry (Light Pink)\n*Lemon Spark (Yellow)\n|Skittles with a spicy kick. \n|December 2017\n|-\n|Skittles Holiday Mix\n|\n* Grape (Green)\n* Green Apple (Light Green)\n* Strawberry (Dark Red)\n* Wild Cherry (Red)\n* Lemon (Light Green)\n|Skittles with a Christmas combo. <Worldwide> colors in red and green\n|December 2015-December 30, 2017\n|-\n|Skittles Love Mix\n|\n* Watermelon (Light Red)\n* White grape (White)\n* Strawberry (Red)\n* Cherry (Dark Red)\n* Yumberry (White)\n|Target-only release\n|January 2018\n|-\n|Skittles Summer Splash\n|\n* Strawberry (pink)\n* Orange (orange)\n* Kiwi Banana (yellow)\n* Watermelon (green)\n* Blue Raspberry (teal)\n|[[Dollar General]]-only release\n|June 2018\n|-\n|Skittles Orchards Limited Edition\n|\n* Cherry (purple)\n* Pomegranate (dark red)\n* Lemon (yellow)\n* Apple (green)\n* Orange (orange)\n|Purchased in the UK - Unsure of other locations and outlets\n|Discovered October 2018\n|-\n|Skittles Sweet Heat Limited Edition ([[United Kingdom]])\n|\n* Piccante Passion Fruit (purple)\n* Sizzlin' Strawberry (red)\n* Lemon Spark (yellow)\n* Fiery Watermelon (pink)\n* Scorchin' Pineapple (orange)\n|Purchased in the [[United Kingdom]] - Unsure of other locations and outlets. <br /> Colors and flavors different from US version. <br /> Sizzlin' Strawberry is red instead of light pink. <br /> Flamin Orange' and Blazin' Mango are replaced by Scorchin' Pineapple and Piccante Passion Fruit, the latter colored purple instead of light orange.\n|Discovered October 2018 - Halloween Special. \n|-\n|Zombie Skittles\n| \n* Petrifying Citrus Punch (Orange)\n* Mummified Melon (Green)\n* Boogeyman Blackberry (Purple?)\n* Chilling Black Cherry (Blue?)\n* Blood Red Berry (Red)\n* Rotten Zombie (Random color)\n|Rotten Zombie flavor mixed in bag.\n|Planned Halloween 2019 in the [[United States of America]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Zombie Skittles Dare You to Taste Rotten Zombie |publisher=The Daily Meal |author=Gael Fashingbauer Cooper |url=https://www.thedailymeal.com/zombie-skittles-taste-like-rotten-zombie|date=2018-10-09 | accessdate=2018-11-30 </ref>\n|-\n|Skittles Imposters\n| \n* Alter Ego Orange \n* Cryptic Citrus\n* Sneaky Strawberry\n* Undercover Apple\n* Raspberry Ruse\n|Share Size and Lay Down Bags, exclusive to Walmart. <br /> Colors don't match the flavors (colors are pink, green, blue, orange, and white).\n|Summer 2019 in the [[United States of America]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mars Wrigley Confectionery Press Kit |publisher=Mars, Incorporated |url=http://www.marswrigleyconfectionerypresskit.com/brand/skittles-candies/|date=2019-05-20 | accessdate=2019-07-12 }}</ref>\n|-\n|Skittles Freeze Pop\n| \n* Blue Raspberry (Teal)\n* Lemon (Yellow)\n* Grape (White)\n* Orange (Orange)\n* Strawberry (Pink)\n|Summer 2019, Singles, exclusive to Dollar General\n|Summer 2019 in the [[United States of America]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mars Wrigley Confectionery Press Kit |publisher=Mars, Incorporated |url=http://www.marswrigleyconfectionerypresskit.com/brand/skittles-candies/|date=2019-05-20 | accessdate=2019-07-12 }}</ref>\n|-\n|Skittles Sour Wild Berry\n| \n* Sour Strawberry\n* Sour Berry Punch\n* Sour Wild Cherry\n* Sour Melon Berry\n* Sour Raspberry\n|Summer 2019, Lay Down Bags, exclusive to Dollar General\n|Summer 2019 in the [[United States of America]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mars Wrigley Confectionery Press Kit |publisher=Mars, Incorporated |url=http://www.marswrigleyconfectionerypresskit.com/brand/skittles-candies/|date=2019-05-20 | accessdate=2019-07-12 }}</ref>\n|-\n|Skittles Chewies\n|\n* Orange\n* Lemon \n* Blackcurrant \n* Strawberry\n* Lime\n|\n|2018 in [[United Kingdom]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.delish.com/food-news/a22560892/skittles-chewies-new/|title=What In The Actual Heck Is Going On With These Very New, Very Naked Skittles??|last=Koman|first=Tess|date=2018-07-26|website=Delish|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n|}\n==References==\n{{portal|Food}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Skittles Products}}\n[[Category:Lists of brand name foods|Skittles]]\n[[Category:American cuisine-related lists|Skittles]]\n[[Category:Dessert-related lists|Skittles]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2012}}\n'''[[Skittles (confectionery)|Skittles]]''' candy products, produced by the [[Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company]], come in a wide variety. Most of the varieties are available only in particular regions of the world. The oldest Skittles product is Original Fruit Skittles, which was originally released in Europe in 1974, and was launched in the United States in 1979.<ref name=\"Wrigley\">{{cite web | title=Skittles | url=http://www.wrigley.com/global/brands/skittles.aspx | work=Wrigley Company | publisher=Wrigley Company | date= | accessdate=2010-07-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121027112505/http://www.wrigley.com/global/brands/skittles.aspx | archive-date=2012-10-27 | url-status=dead }}</ref> The most recent flavor, Sweet Heat, was released in 2018. Earlier Skittles products tended to focus on fruit flavors, more recent products have branched out to include flavors such as chocolate, bubble gum, popcorn, mint, and sours. Skittles products also come in a wide variety of colors, although different Skittles products often use the same colors for sweets with different flavors. For example, the color yellow is associated with lemon flavor in Original Fruit Skittles and as banana berry in Tropical Skittles.\n\nThe original Skittles in the United States were orange, lemon, lime, grape and strawberry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrigley.com/global/brands/skittles.aspx |title=Skittles &#124; Skittles Flavors &#124; Skittles Candy |publisher=Wrigley.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121027112505/http://www.wrigley.com/global/brands/skittles.aspx |archive-date=2012-10-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In the United States Skittles lime was changed to green apple.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/todayilearned/comments/1arqcv/til_that_the_green_skittle_is_now_apple_flavored/ |title=TIL that the green skittle apple : todayilearned |publisher=Reddit.com |date=2013-03-22 |accessdate=2017-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodbeast.com/news/skittles-swaps-green-apple-flavor-with-lime-changes-original-rainbow/ |title=Skittles Swaps Green Apple Flavor with Lime, Changes 'Original' Rainbow |publisher=Foodbeast.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-07}}</ref> A \"Long Lost Lime\" variation of Skittles has been released in summer 2017 and 2018, bringing the lime flavor back to the original mix of Skittles for a limited time only.\n\n==List==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| '''Name'''\n| '''Colors and flavors'''\n| '''Notes'''\n| '''Year'''\n|-\n| Original Skittles\n|\n* [[Blackcurrant]], [[Kiwifruit]], or [[Grape]] (purple), ''see notes''\n* [[Lemon]] (yellow)\n* [[Apple|Green Apple]] or [[Lime (fruit)|Lime]] (green), ''see notes''\n* [[Orange (fruit)|Orange]] (orange)\n* [[Strawberry]] (red)\n* [[Cherry cola]] (blue)   ''Included in a limited edition in the UK.''\n| In [[Ireland]], the [[United Kingdom]], Sweden and [[Germany]] purple Skittles are [[blackcurrant]]. <br />\nIn [[Taiwan]], [[South Korea]], [[China]], [[Australia]], and, as of 2013, the [[United States of America]] Lime is replaced with Green Apple flavor.<br /> Lime was moved to the \"Darkside\" flavor in 2013 (but called \"Midnight Lime\" in said product Darkside Skittles).\nGreen Apple also replaced Lime in the [[United States of America]] for a brief time in April 2001, as part of a promotion.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Great Skittle Debate |publisher=February-7.com |author=JPS |url=http://www.february-7.com/index.asp?cat=Personal |accessdate=2008-03-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20030219095950/http://www.february-7.com/index.asp?cat=Personal |archivedate=February 19, 2003 }}</ref> In 2013, this change was made permanent.\n| 1974<ref name=\"Wrigley\" />\n|-\n| Tropical (Rainforest)\n|\n* [[Banana]] [[Berry]] (yellow)\n* [[Kiwifruit|Kiwi]] [[Lime (fruit)|Lime]] (green)\n* [[Mango]] [[Tangelo]] (orange)\n* [[Pineapple]] [[Passion fruit]] (blue)\n* [[Strawberry]] [[Carambola|Starfruit]] (pink)\n|Tropical Skittles typically have two flavors in one skittle.<ref name=\"Wrigley\" /><!-- The product is sold in either light blue bags or boxes; originally, they came in red-orange bags or boxes. importance? -->\n| 1989<ref name=\"Wrigley\" />\n|-\n| Wild Berry \n|\n* [[Berry]] [[Punch (drink)|Punch]] (violet)\n* [[Melon]] [[Berry]] (green)\n* [[Raspberry]] (blue)\n* [[Strawberry]] (pink)\n* [[Cherry|Wild Cherry]] (red)\n|Was launched in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]] in 2012 and in the UK in 2014. A variant with fizzy powder existed in 2010-2011 (known as Fizzl'd Fruits), but some of the colors were changed.\n| 1989<ref name=\"Wrigley\" />\n|-\n| Tart-N-Tangy\n| Flavors were those that represent the sour Skittles that were released after these were discontinued with slight differences to the flavors. Specifics on the flavors are sketchy.\n| Discontinued in 1992. Was later replaced by Sour Skittles in the bright green package. \n| 1989\n|-\n| Crazy Cores\n|(shell color, core)\n* [[Blue raspberry flavor|Blue Raspberry]] [[Lemon]] (B, Y)\n* [[Cherry]] [[Lemonade]] (R, Y)\n* [[Mango]] [[Peach]] (O, R)\n* [[Melon]] [[Berry]] (P, G)\n* [[Strawberry]] [[Watermelon]] (G, P)\n|Sold in bulk stores in the U.S. (e.g., [[Sam's Club]])<br> Introduced in the [[United Kingdom]] in 2011. Withdrawn from the UK in 2013, replaced by Confused Skittles\n| 2008<ref name=\"Mars press release\">[http://www.prnewswire.com/mnr/mars/35287/ Mars Press Release]</ref>/2011 (UK) \n|-\n| Skittles Confused\n| The flavors were meant to be Fruit Skittles with the colors and flavors mixed up, showing the answers on the back.\n| Skittles with mixed up flavors and colors. Sold for a short time in the [[United Kingdom]] in 2008. They came in purple bags with a large question mark.\n| 2008\n|-\n\n| Confused?\n| Similar to an incarnation previously sold in the [[United Kingdom]] where the same colored shell can contain different flavors, a green piece may be cherry in one bag, and peach in another.\n* [[Blue raspberry flavor|Blue Raspberry]]\n* [[Cherry]]\n* [[Lemon]]\n* [[Mango]] + [[Peach]]\n* [[Lime (fruit)|Lime]]\n* [[Watermelon]]\n* [[Mandarin orange|Mandarin]]\n* [[Blueberry]]\n* [[Raspberry]]\n* [[Melon]] [[Berry]]\n*\n|Part of the 2013 [[United Kingdom]] brand re-launch. Carried the tagline 'Confuse the Rainbow, Taste the Rainbow' \n| \n|-\n\n| Sour\n|\n* [[Grape|Sour Grape]] (purple)\n* [[Lime (fruit)|Sour Lime]] (green)*\n* [[